From 561053a3fea0a5eacacbea290cabb00b46813193 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Detmar Ruhfus <detmar.ruhfus@aogroup.co.za>
Date: Mon, 16 Feb 2026 20:24:26 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix: Complete async step execution in Celery workers

This fixes the critical bug where workflows with ASYNC steps failed with:
'NoneType' object has no attribute 'workflow_builder'

Root causes:
1. Template engine import path was incorrect (template_engine vs templating)
2. Celery workers lacked full provider initialization (only had persistence)
3. SyncExecutor tried to access workflow_builder via _engine (which was None)
4. Async step results weren't being merged into workflow state

Changes:
- src/rufus/celery_app.py: Fixed import path for Jinja2TemplateEngine
- src/rufus/tasks.py: Added global providers and set_providers() function
- src/rufus/implementations/execution/sync.py: Fixed WorkflowBuilder import
- src/rufus/workflow.py: Added result merge for AsyncWorkflowStep
- pyproject.toml: Bumped version to 0.3.7

Docker improvements:
- Added Dockerfile.rufus-server-local for local development
- Added Dockerfile.rufus-worker-local for local development
- Added Dockerfile.rufus-server-alembic with migration support
- Added entrypoint-server.sh for Alembic migrations

Testing:
- Verified all providers initialize in worker processes
- Tested ASYNC step execution with result merge
- Confirmed workflow completes successfully through all steps

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
